cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the secure delegation of eviction in Oblivious RAM. It could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it proposes a design inspired by mix-net technologies. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with Oblivious RAM, which is a data structure. It could also be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as Oblivious RAM is known to have high overhead, which is a complexity concern. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it proposes a system design for secure delegation of eviction in Oblivious RAM.
